<br>
We have the problem that our guildleader is missing in action (see another post where we were looking for another one).  He has been since 2 months now, and shows no sign(s) of himself nor of his return.<br>
<br>
We have just 2 officers left active in the guild, others have left.  <br>
Without a leader we cannot make new officers, though 3 have been voted into the position by the guild.<br>
<br>
Have any of you had any experience with getting Sony to actually transfer leadership to someone else somehow, disabling the missing leader's guildleadership?<br>
<br>
We are desperate and would appreciate any advise.<br>
We had a guildmeeting yesterday in-game and decided not to reform into another guild but to keep at it until at least Christmas.  <br>
But any advise as to how to speed these things up is well appreciated.<br>
<br>
We have e-mailed Sony via their official Everquest pages and have petitioned in-game, but so far to no avail.<br>
<br>
We will keep at it though, but do you happen to know another tactic?<br>
<br>
Maybe you too can ask Sony to bestow leadership on any of the following members of the Gnomish Alliance of Gnomes (Tokeymi, Yanari, Malliss or Dukvodju)?  <br>
<br>
Maybe the fact that some other people care about it too will go a long way to speeding things up.<br>
<br>
Thank you in advance for any replies and/or advise.<br>
<br>
Yanari Pethugger,<br>
Gnomish Alliance of Gnomes Officer. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=faias>Faias</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 8<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(11/18/02 6:40 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm47.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=359.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Transfer of leadership in a guild - anyone with exp on i</span><hr size=1> I belive Hailhammer has experience with this, he succesfully gained leadership of the halfheight heroes after a smiliar situation, allthough I was not a member at the time. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=yanaripethugger>Yanari Pethugger</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 19<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(11/18/02 6:51 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm47.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=359.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Transfer of leadership in a guild </span><hr size=1> Thanks Faias,<br>
